Session: sem-equiv-checker (2026-04-03)
Agent: Cam

## What was done

Built the semantic equivalence checker as `codex sem-equiv` in the reference
compiler CLI (`tools/Codex.Cli/Program.SemEquiv.cs`). Pure text processing,
no compiler library dependencies.

Usage:
```
dotnet run --project tools/Codex.Cli -- sem-equiv <stage0> <stage1> [--show <name>]
```

Features:
- Parses stage0 with module markers, stage1 flat
- De-mangles scoped names (42 collisions, longest-prefix-first matching)
- Assigns stage1 defs to modules (by demangling or stage0 lookup)
- Matches defs per module, reports drops/extras
- Compares signatures with type-variable alpha-normalization
- Compares bodies after whitespace collapse, demangling, paren normalization
- Per-module summary table with Body% column
- `--show <name>` drills into individual defs (shows normalized S0/S1 side by side)
- Exit 0 = PASS, 1 = FAIL

