- tools/Codex.Cli/Program.SemEquiv.cs — the checker (new)
- tools/Codex.Cli/Program.cs — wired up "sem-equiv" command
- Codex.Codex/Emit/CodexEmitter.codex — emit-expr needs precedence parens
- Codex.Codex/Emit/CSharpEmitter.codex — escape-text needs brace handling
- docs/TestResults/stage0.codex, stage1.codex — current test artifacts

## Key learnings
- `}` at column 0 in record literals needs special handling in def parsers
- Type variable names differ between stages (alpha-normalize for comparison)
- `(if ...)` parens are cosmetic (stripped in normalizer)
- `(a + b)` parens around binary sub-expressions are NOT cosmetic when the
  parent op has higher precedence — dropping them changes semantics
